Example of using CreDating

Xavier Didelot

2017-10-16

Initialisation

library(CreDating)
library(ape)
set.seed(0)

Data

We consider a random timed tree with 20 leaves, with the root in 2000.

nsam <- 20
phy <- rtree(nsam, br = rexp)
phy$root.time <- 2000
plot(phy)
axisPhylo(backward = F)

We can extract the sampling dates.

dates = leafDates(phy)
#dates[seq(2,20,2)]=NA#Oops, just lost half of the dates!

On each branch we observe a number of substitutions which is distributed \(\mathrm{Poisson}(rl)\) where \(l\) is the branch length and \(r=10\) per year is the real substitution rate.

obsphy=phy
obsphy$root.time=NULL
#obsphy$edge.length=unlist(lapply(obsphy$edge.length*10,function (x) rpois(1,x)))
obsphy$edge.length=unlist(lapply(obsphy$edge.length*10,function (x) rgamma(1,x,1)))
res=roottotip(obsphy,dates,predInt='gamma',showTree=T)

Unknown root

Lets say we dont know where the root is, we might consider as a guess that it is at the midpoint:

obsphy=phangorn::midpoint(obsphy)
res=roottotip(obsphy, dates, predInt = 'gamma', showTree = T)

Analysis

We run CreDating as follows:

res=credate(obsphy,dates,nbIts = 20000,model=3,findRoot = 2)
plot(res)

Plot with credibility bars:

plot(res,'treeCI')

We can see what the MCMC traces look like:

plot(res,'trace')
